Four students from Syokisinga mixed secondary school in Machakos on Friday drowned in River Athi near Katangi. One body has been retrieved and search for the others is ongoing. "Three boys and one girl, all form one students from Syokisinga mixed secondary school have died in River Athi. They had gone for a Geography class (field work) with their teacher when they drowned while swimming," Yatta sub-county education director Stephen Kitungu said. KUPPET executive secretary, Machakos Musembi Katuku sent his message of condolence to the bereaved families. "I have learned of the drowning of four form one students of Syokisinga secondary school with a lot of shock and disbelief. It is unfortunate that we have lost young and tender souls," said Katuku.